Jayco, Inc., a subsidiary of Thor Industries that manufacturers recreation vehicles including fold-down camping trailers, conventional travel trailers, toy hauliers, fifth-wheel travel trailers, and motorhomes recently announced the groundbreaking of a new 1,500-square-foot health clinic that will be a part of the Jayco Holistic Health Facility, which includes a fitness facility and occupational clinic. Covering a total of 10,000 square feet the Jayco holistic health facility features all areas of general and preventative health care and it has physicians and nurses who will provide primary care and preventative health services, as well as prescription medications and wellness coaching. Also Read: Construction plans on new IU Health medical complex released, Indiana The facility is reportedly unique to the area, and it will be widely available, extremely easy to use and make appointments, including select evening and Saturday visits. The new health clinic and Jayco holistic health facility at large will serve workers and dependents of the Jayco Family of Companies, which includes Entegra Coach, Jayco, Starcraft RV, and Highland Ridge RV. Speaking on the project Adam Tohulka, a DJ Construction spokesman said “We are thrilled to be a part of this project and to build on our long-standing partnerships with Goshen Health and Jayco. It’s exciting to watch Goshen Health, Jayco, and DJ Construction work together to design and build this new clinic that will serve the Jayco campus with the great care that Goshen Health is recognized for.” Jon Yoder, vice president of the Goshen Physicians Network on the other hand said, “Over the years, we’ve enjoyed collaborating with Jayco to deliver occupational medicine on their campus. We are now thrilled to be working with them on this expansion to provide primary care services to their employees and their families. By working together, we can enhance the health of our community.”